{"body": "> I am definitely confused then, since drop_table :foo is much simple than revert { create_table :foo }.\r\n\r\nIt is simpler, except that:\r\n* `drop_table` is not revertible\r\n* if you have a bunch of `create_table`, `rename_column`, etc..., in a migration and you later want to undo that migration because you changed your mind, it's easier to enclose the commands in a `revert {}` than to modify each command *and* reverse their order.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/9825825", "created_at": "2012-10-26T20:24:43Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7627#issuecomment-9825825", "updated_at": "2012-10-26T20:24:43Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7627, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/marcandre", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/marcandre", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/b06d8e26b92456b228d3c77b66397534?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F8b48ea597d2862688e4aa8a2b28651a3.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/received_events", "gravatar_id": "b06d8e26b92456b228d3c77b66397534", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "marcandre", "type": "User", "id": 33770, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/marcandre/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523dda17bd354364b900aaee"}, "id": 9825825, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7627"}
